This activity could involve practising complex social skills in simulated social situations. Before the beginning of this activity, participants would be asked to list feared situations in a hierarchy, beginning with least feared to highly difﬁcult. Then the participant and the robot would engage in a simulation of a feared social situation. The social robot could be programmed to demonstrate speciﬁc verbal and nonverbal behaviours associated with the role. For example, if the simulated social situation is a job interview, the robot would presume the role of the interviewer. The robot could also provide verbal positive reinforcement to encourage participants and build their conﬁdence

