Elizabeth Nilsen Ph.D., C. Psych., is a Professor within the Department of Psychology at the University of Waterloo. She is the Director of the Cognitive Development Lab with a research focus on children and adolescents’ sensitivity to the mental states of conversational partners and the social and cognitive skills that allow youth to engage successfully with others. She is also a Clinical Psychologist and supervises the clinical activities of graduate students within the University of Waterloo’s Centre for Mental Health Research and Treatment.

Publisher’s Note Springer Nature remains neutral with regard to jurisdictional claims in published maps and institutional afﬁliations.
Samira Rasouli is a Ph.D. student in the Electrical and Computer Engineering Department at the University of Waterloo. She is afﬁliated with the Social and Intelligent Robotics Research Laboratory (SIRRL). Her main research interests are in human-robot interaction, social robotics, and artiﬁcial intelligence. Her research explores potential applications of social robots as assistive tools for supporting mental well-being.

Kerstin Dautenhahn IEEE Fellow, is Full Professor and Canada 150 Research Chair in Intelligent Robotics at University of Waterloo in Ontario, Canada. She has a joint appointment with the Departments of Electrical and Computer Engineering and Systems Design Engineering and is cross-appointed with the David R. Cheriton School of Computer Science at University of Waterloo. In Waterloo she directs the Social and Intelligent Robotics Laboratory. Her research areas are social robotics, human-robot interaction, assistive robotics, cognitive and developmental robotics.

Garima Gupta is an undergraduate student majoring in psychology with a research-intensive specialization at the University of Waterloo. She has been afﬁliated with the Social and Intelligent Robotics Research Laboratory (SIRRL) since 2019. Her research at SIRRL is focused on mapping the application of social robots onto supports for chronic medical and psychological conditions.

